So I never made it to the RHH show, because Friday night I got knocked down 

(it was a total accident, the guy didn't see me at all) and I landed on my face.  I broke some teeth, loosened a couple of others up, and basically hurt my mouth really badly.  I was in a lot of pain still yesterday and was still swollen so my dentist sent me to an oral surgeon this morning just to be on the safe side, as they thought I may have fractured my face (Pixies song, anyone?).

It turns out that I didn't break anymore in my face or mouth than they had thought, but I have severely bruised the bone.  That's why I am in so much pain.  He says that there really isn't anything they can do, that I just have to wait for it to go away, and then my regular dentist will fix my front teeth.  He said to take it easy, put me on Naproxen as well as the Vicodin, and told me I wasn't a pussy, that I should be in pain.  He also put me on penicillin, as he said that there have been studies that show it speeds healing in dental injuries.
 

Meh.  Like Ian says "Hooray for good drugs!" Meh.

So . . . where does one find a dress that covers them all??  It sucks, I have beautifull dresses that could be perfect for this sort of thing, except they show one or two or three or more.  I guess I can try H&M or Filene's Basement **shudders**   

Have any of my Goth-Girl friends ever had to deal with this, what did you wear???  Yeah, I probably should have started worrying about this before today, but procrastination is the mother of invention.  Also I hate, hate, hate shopping in "normal" stores.

Any advice from anyone will be greatly appreciated.  Prizes will be given for useful answers.  Cookies given for snarky/funny ones!


ETA:  H & M saves the day.  They had a really cute sweater-type dress with a cowl neck and slightly extra long sleeves.  It will look rather elegant with some jewelry I have, a nisce pair of boots or heels and a very pretty evening scarf.  The Bar Mitzvah starts at 5 and goes until late late late.

Okay so it is finally sunny outside, but I feel like warmed over shit inside my head.  Physically I feel fine.  I feel like I can't quite get a grasp on the things going on in my life.  I have this distinct out-of-control feeling but I am not actually doing anything that would seem out of control.  I am very overwhelmed by everything.  When I sit down to talk to people about it to try to get a grasp on it and bounce my theories ont them to see what the hell is going on, they pretty much tell me that I am just thinking too much.  Which I can believe, because alot has changed over the last 4 months.  What's funny is that, despite a recent blow to my ego, almost all the change has been either extremly good or exactly what I wanted to happen.  So why do I feel so overwhelmed?  I think that in part it is that I am succeeding in my life exactly how I have always wanted it and I am getting older and now part of me rally needs to act like an adult and be responsible ALL the time.  Those of you who know me are familiar with my devil-may-care fuck-'em-if-they-can't-take-a-joke philosophy that has been the better part of my life.  I have always survived, but I was rarely happy.  Now I have everything in front of me to be happy, it is all right in my grasp and I am FREAKING out.  I just need to get rid of one more of the bad aspects and get on the ball of a couple of others, and I will be and have everything that I wanted or needed.  Yes folks, I know what's the problem.  There really is none, I just guess I have issues with everything going so well, I am waiting for the other shoe to drop.  Then there is the part of me that actually trys to make the shoe drop so at least I won't have to worry about it anymore.  Am I one of those people that has to have major issues in their life just to pacify themselves with the thought that "Oh, I knew something would get fucked up".  I would hate to think that.  I don't like people like that, drama-queens/kings.  Meh.   I just really need to chill the fuck out and focus this seemingly abundant energy on the things that REALLY matter to me.  And I need to stop being so fucking scared that I am going to lose him, he has done everything possible to show me that he isn't going anywhere, so I just need to stop looking for hidden signals that things are going wrong and just give myself permission to be happy.  ARGH!!!!!!!  

Postscriptum:  Sorry for the insanity, but I did promise someone that I would start updating more frequently and this is what has been on my mind for the past few days . . .

Okay, so I haven't posted in like a millenia or so.  Yeah I suck a little, but a lot has been going on. . .

Uhm, let's see, I moved back into the city in October, been kind of scattered ever since until now.
Was in a relationship with a wonderful man who introduced me to a wonderful community.  However, it was obvious that neither of us were the other's 'one' so he broke it off with me.  This led me to where I am at now. . .

I am actually, for the first time ever, brace yourself folks, I am IN LOVE!!!!!!   Crazy as that may seem. Veronica, the international girly-swinger, is off the market, forever.  I actually managed to find my soul-mate.  Didn't mean to, wasn't even looking for anything.  Totally out of the blue.  The only thing that has been a downside is that this person is a friend of the one who broke it off with me.  And we haven't spoken since I got together with said soul-mate.  I really don't want there to be any bad feelings, I really miss this person as a friend and confidant.

I am ecstatic in my love and in my world, and want to share it with people who would want to know.  It is the single most amazing thing that has ever happened to me.  
Mioux,
V

So folks, when we last left our heroine she was going to go run in her new trail runners.  Yeah!  Okay, so dad and I decided to go about 4.5 miles and I got blisters.  Blah, oh well.  Now they have healed, but, I HAVE A JOB!!!!!    Wooohoo.  I got hired by COAN oil in Natick as the Receptionist/Administrative Assistant.  It is a pretty good job.  I like it because I am busy constantly and the people are very nice.  It is refreshing to not go to work every morning with the feeling of dread underscored with the feeling of what did I do that I am going to get in trouble for today.  But that also means that trail running has been pushed to a weekend only sort of thing.
Things are going well.  I started work last Monday, the fourth so I get paid for the first time tomorrow.  It has been a while since I had money coming in, so this is a very good thing.  I am also psyched because Circuit City is having a sale on their CD's Thursday, Friday and Saturday. they will all be 9.99 for the grand opening of their new locatiuon, so needless to say some of my money is already allocated . . .
Not much going on in the social scene, which is driving me crazy, but I also don't have my license thing yet, so I can't drive any where anyway.  So I shall save my money and wait until I can grace the scene with my presence once more.
I have a cold.  Blah.  I haven't been sick in so long, I didn't even know what was wrong with me until my mom mentioned it.  I just thought that I was depressed, turns out that I wasn't any more depressed than normal, I was just coming down with an old fashioned, run of the mill, cold.  Thank Goddess for Puffs tissues.  They are saving my nose, which would surely be swiss cheese now if I had to use normal tissues.  As soon as my immune system is back up to its normal running stage, I am going to do a major detox/fast to PURIFY, so i can start toxifying all over again, tee hee.

There was so much that I wanted to do today, and I didn't get any of it done.  Dad and I went to help my grandparents, they are selling their house top move into a more wheelchair convenient type place.  I guess that is good.  Unfortunately, they have lived in the house they are in for the last 28 years or so.  Lots of stuff to go through.  
We got home around 1pm and then ate some lunch and stuff and by the time I was out of the shower and everything it was 3.  Had to go out and pick up dad's new glasses, and he wanted to get some waterproof trail runners for me to go into the woods, because we both hate to run on the roads.  Then back to the house and it was like 4:30 and I just finished catching up on computer stuff and have done absolutely nothing I needed to do.  Oh well, at least I got to help out my Grandparents, they needed it.
Not much else.  Can't wait to try out my new trail runners, fun in the woods with DRY feet!!!!

Well, my darlings, if you haven't heard the rumous already, let me tell you . . .

  I am moving back to Massachusetts.  I am already here, as a matter of fact.  I came to visit and then realized that I didn't want to go back to Georgia.  Not because I don't love all of my friends there and especially not because I didn't love my fabulous boyfriend, more that I wasn't doing myself any good there.  
  Yes, Craig and I broke up, but only because I need a relationship with another person right now just about as much as another hole in the head.  I still love Craig very much and talk to him almost every day, but I need to work on another relationship that is a lot more important.  The relationship I need to have with myself and my relationship with the powers that be in my life.  
  For the last 15 years or so, I have been in one relationship or another.  I have not been single even once.  Because of this, I have been constantly living for someone else.  I found, when I arrived in MA, that I really didn't have that great a grasp on who I actually was.  I couldn't even figure out what I actually liked or wanted, because I had spent so much of my life living for others.  Not good.  I am not even really sure how or why so many people dated me, because I couldn't have been that great of a girlfriend, if I didn't even have that great of a relationship with myself.   But alas, that is where I stand.
  I am going to be living with my parents until I get enough money saved to rent a small apartment nearby, all the while nurturing my relationship with myself and my family and getting on the path of what I really want to do.
  I am always going to be a work in progress, we all are, but it would help if I knew who that work was.  So, as cliche as it sounds, I have left to find myself.  
  Now for a less deep update . . .
  Ok, so the state of GA has totally fucked up my ability to get my license renewed, because of some trouble that happened four years ago that they never told me about or sent me anything or anything like that.  It turns out that I have been driving on a suspended license for the last FOUR years.  And no one told me, not even when I got pulled over 3 times.  And now I am trying to get a document from Robins AFB to try and clear up the confusion, and they are totally dicking me over and not sending it.  I need to get a JOB, people, and although getting a job doesn't completely hinge on me having a valid drivers license, it sure as shit would help.
  So I am helping around the house with my Mom and Dad and my little brother and sister, it is cool.  At first I thought it was going to be really weird moving back home whilst I get on my feet, being that I am 30 and all, but it really isn't that weird.  And every one is being really cool and supportive and all, so it's good.  They TOTALLY acknowledge my need to regroup and put myself back together.  I guess that it also helps that they aren't that much older than me.  They also know how much I have been through, and have told me that for their own piece of mind, they rather I be here to go through all of this.  
  I have been walking (REALLY fast) 4 miles everyday with my dad and the dog Freddie (my dad named him after Freddie Mercury).  I am about to start up yoga again and doing a whole bunch of other stuff as well.  It's good.  I am trying to put my resume together again for the first time in like 7 years, and that is rather hard and annoying, but I have found a number of helpful references online and in print form.  I am going to finish it tonight and start job hunting tomorrow with some help from my mom's closet, because I originally came up here to visit, not stay.  All I have for clothing are jeans and T-shirts, not exactly interview wear.
  One of the other reasons I decided to move back here was that my aunt died not so long ago, and then my cousin died.  My aunt was in her 30's, but it was terminal cancer.  My cousin was in his 50's and it was a heart attack.  My grandmother has had a stroke and surgery and stuff and she is in a wheelchair or with a walker, and all this stuff made me realize that you really can't take family for granted, because they die, or get damaged.  So I figured for my own piece of mind, I ought to live as close as I can in order to be here to help and to spend time, and all that.
  Okay this entry is turning into a megalong one, so I will end it here . . .

You ever get the feeling that you pissed someone off and the universe didn't like it and now you are paying the price?  Yeah, so due to some stupid BITCH being an absolute freakin moron in front of my Manager on Wednesday, I lost my bartending gig at Liz Reed's.  Yeah, "we have to let you go, because even though we know you probably didn't do what she said you did, if she starts to talk people won't be able to trust the bartenders here, blah, blah, blah"  I think there was an alternative motive, but I can't prove my theory, so whatever.  And this customer is one who REPEATEDLY walks out on her tab and only comes back to pay it sometimes.  It is very possibly the stupidist thing I have ever delt with besides the mlitary.  I have never been fired before.  It really makes you feel worthless, even if it wasn't your fault, but the fact that you would be fired for something like that makes you feel pretty inconsequential.  SO let's take stock, shall we?  The military still hasn't gotten me my orders (It's been 10 days now for those who are counting), One of my favorite cousins died (he was only 42), and I lost my job at Liz's.  All this among several other minor things, and I am just ready to curl up in a ball with a bottle of Tequila and not exist anymore.  And would everyone please stop trying to cheer me up.  I appreciate the sentiment, but I will be happy again at some point, just not right now.    ARRRRRRRRRRRRRRRRRGH

Okay, we all know that the government for the most part is relatively fucked, right?  But why are they doing this to me.  I was supposed to be discharged early last week, and now I have been waiting 9, yes count them - 9, days for my discharge orders.  Why, if they can discharge someone in 48 hours, do I have to wait this long.  I am on pause.  It is fucking ridiculous.  I have never delt with something so incredibly stupid in my entire life.  This has been the biggest waste of time, I have ever encountered in my life, and to top it all off, I can't even call anyone to try and find out what the hold up is, because one of my superiors has already told me that I need to stop bothering people because they have more important things to do.  I ask you, kind LJ folks, how hard is it to sign something and transport it to another office on the base???  They could even fax it, but Noooooooooooo, they have not.  I have never been so frustrated, I fucking hate this more than anything I have experienced yet.  Those of you who know me, know that I only joined the military for school, and then they started screwing me over this year, and I got in a whole mess o trouble, and now they are supposed to be discharging me.  What's a girl gotta do to speed shit up around here?  All this ends up doing, is stop me from interviewing for much more desirable jobs and to have to work doubles to get the shifts at the one other job I did get so far.  So now from 6 am this morning to 3 am Saturday morning, I will have approximately 2-3 hours of sleep in between bartending and coming into this hell-hole.  If you are bored come visit me at Liz Reed's Music Hall on Cherry St. in Macon, GA.  I will be there from 5pm to 2am today, Thurs. and Fri.  Bring me some happiness and some thing to soothe my frustrated soul.  On a good note, it is Metal-Fest this Friday, so much fun will be had by all!!!  On a bad note, I found out yesterday that my super-cool cousin died on Monday.  Blah.

HOW FUCKING STUPID IS THAT!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

I really don't know what the hell is wrong with me.
